A
n\times n
\lim_{n \to \infty} \left(I + \frac{A}{n}\right)^{n} = e^{A}.
 \lim_{n \to \infty} \left(I + \left(\frac{A}{n} \right)^{n} \right) = \lim_{n \to \infty} \sum_{k=0}^{n} \binom{n}{k} I^{k} \left(\frac{A}{n} \right)^{n-k}
=  \lim_{n \to \infty} \sum_{k=0}^{n} \binom{n}{k} \left(\frac{A}{n} \right)^{n-k}
